WEBVTT

00:18.017 --> 00:19.102
<i>Previously on </i>You:

00:19.185 --> 00:21.563
<i>"Hello, you."</i>
<i>Of course you're using Evanesce.</i>

00:21.646 --> 00:25.525
<i>No reverse lookup,</i> <i>messages disappear</i>
<i>after they've been read.</i>

00:25.608 --> 00:27.444
<i>A favorite of the elite and the paranoid.</i>

00:27.527 --> 00:30.947
I suppose I'll see you
at that stupid art show, professor.

00:31.865 --> 00:32.949
<i>Kate Galvin.</i>

00:33.033 --> 00:34.701
-Go away.
-<i>Kate gives little.</i>

00:34.784 --> 00:36.578
That jacket makes you look like a waiter.

00:36.661 --> 00:39.289
You are a hollow nobody
with no life of his own.

00:39.372 --> 00:42.459
-Malcolm. He made us call him that.
-<i>Was she just a student?</i>

00:42.542 --> 00:44.753
-What do you want?
-<i>Nadia was right.</i>

00:44.836 --> 00:46.921
<i>The first suspect is usually</i>
<i>the second victim.</i>

00:47.005 --> 00:49.132
<i>"I'll figure you out soon enough."</i>

00:54.721 --> 00:56.222
<i>"Hello, Joe."</i>

01:02.312 --> 01:06.483
<i>It's times like these I can't help</i>
<i>but wonder, where did I go wrong?</i>

01:08.359 --> 01:09.903
<i>All I wanted was a holiday</i>

01:10.487 --> 01:12.989
<i>to start my new life, good,</i>

01:13.073 --> 01:16.910
<i>honest, peaceful,</i>
<i>but you've destroyed that.</i>

01:16.993 --> 01:18.828
<i>You violated my safe haven,</i>

01:18.912 --> 01:22.332
<i>dredging up the me</i>
<i>I've been trying hard to leave behind.</i>

01:27.045 --> 01:30.507
<i>"Am I right?</i>
<i>Are all those articles about you?"</i>

01:32.425 --> 01:34.761
<i>Obviously, I can't say yes.</i> <i>Come on.</i>

01:34.844 --> 01:36.846
<i>My name is Jonathan Moore.</i>

01:39.140 --> 01:41.476
<i>"Come on, Joe. Tell me the truth."</i>

01:45.855 --> 01:49.234
<i>I refuse to fuel</i>
<i>your sick and misguided fixation.</i>

01:50.902 --> 01:54.030
<i>I'm supposed to be finding you,</i>
<i>not changing my locks.</i>

01:58.701 --> 02:02.413
<i>But I have to keep you out</i>
<i>of my flat, of my mind.</i>

02:06.751 --> 02:08.002
<i>"Are you ignoring me?</i>

02:09.838 --> 02:11.339
<i>You're hurting my feelings, Joe.</i>

02:12.465 --> 02:13.550
<i>Are you there?"</i>

02:13.633 --> 02:14.926
<i>Are you there?</i>

02:15.009 --> 02:16.719
<i>You've left me no choice.</i>

02:18.012 --> 02:19.722
<i>I gotta ghost you, stalker.</i>

02:23.726 --> 02:25.395
<i>In Poe's "Man of the Crowd,"</i>

02:25.937 --> 02:28.398
<i>the narrator sees a random stranger</i>
<i>in a caf√©</i>

02:28.481 --> 02:30.441
and becomes obsessed with him.

02:31.151 --> 02:33.361
So he follows the stranger
through the streets of London.

02:33.444 --> 02:34.362
He's making deductions.

02:34.445 --> 02:37.657
But why he's interested remains,
oh, ambiguous.

02:37.740 --> 02:41.578
So thoughts on what this story
is saying about obsession?

02:42.328 --> 02:44.581
That it goes hand in hand
with the urge to protect.

02:45.081 --> 02:47.083
The narrator follows the stranger
because he sees him

02:47.167 --> 02:49.627
-hiding a dagger under his clothes.
-<i>Correct. But obvious.</i>

02:49.711 --> 02:52.422
-Interesting. What else?
-It's about love.

02:52.505 --> 02:55.383
-Sure you read the right story?
-It's about the kind of love

02:55.466 --> 02:58.928
that you have for something
you'll never fully understand.

02:59.554 --> 03:03.391
-This is about fixation.
-Who says they're mutually exclusive?

03:03.474 --> 03:07.562
The narrator wants to connect
and to know and to be known, right?

03:07.645 --> 03:12.650
-That's why he stalks a stranger.
-Sorry, but it's about Professor Harding.

03:12.734 --> 03:14.819
Fuck me. He's been murdered.

03:14.903 --> 03:18.156
They think it's connected
to the Simon Soo art-gallery murder.

03:18.239 --> 03:19.115
<i>Oh, no.</i>

03:19.198 --> 03:21.659
They're calling him
the "eat-the-rich killer." Catchy.

03:24.078 --> 03:26.581
<i>Malcolm Harding's finger was sent</i>
<i>to </i>The London Dispatch

03:26.664 --> 03:29.959
<i>with a note discerning, "This is not</i>
<i>a kidnapping. This is a murder."</i>

03:30.543 --> 03:31.920
<i>Well, fuck.</i>

03:33.421 --> 03:35.715
<i>You didn't keep Malcolm's pinkie</i>
<i>as a trophy,</i>

03:35.798 --> 03:37.884
<i>you're using it to force me</i>
<i>to play your game.</i>

03:37.967 --> 03:40.094
<i>-This is very, very bad.</i>

03:41.054 --> 03:43.348
<i>"Now do I have your attention?"</i>

03:51.397 --> 03:53.733
<i>Okay, asshole, you've made your point.</i>

03:54.317 --> 03:57.195
<i>I've canceled the rest of my class,</i>
<i>so my students can process their shock,</i>

03:57.278 --> 04:01.783
<i>aka gossip about the eat-the-rich killer</i>
<i>targeting these well-to-dos.</i>

04:02.742 --> 04:05.578
<i>So, yes, you have my attention.</i>

04:06.162 --> 04:08.915
<i>The question is, "What do you want?"</i>

04:11.167 --> 04:12.835
<i>"Admit you're Joe Goldberg."</i>

04:12.919 --> 04:16.589
<i>Ah, well, that's not happening,</i>
<i>but I also can't refuse to engage.</i>

04:16.673 --> 04:18.800
<i>So: "I'm not.</i>

04:19.550 --> 04:22.136
<i>But if I was,</i>
<i>what</i> <i>would</i> <i>you</i> <i>want</i> <i>from</i> <i>me?"</i>

04:27.392 --> 04:29.894
<i>"For starters,</i>
<i>why'd you kill all those people?</i>

04:31.229 --> 04:33.898
<i>Should mention, still have Simon's ear.</i>

04:33.982 --> 04:36.234
<i>Shall I send</i>
<i>with a note signed 'Jonathan Moore'?"</i>

04:36.317 --> 04:38.319
<i>And there it is, blackmail.</i>

04:38.861 --> 04:42.156
<i>Okay. Okay, say as little as possible.</i>

04:43.032 --> 04:45.201
<i>"If I had done these things,</i>

04:45.285 --> 04:48.579
<i>it could only have been</i>
<i>because I had no other options."</i>

04:51.499 --> 04:53.251
<i>"Ah. It was life or death."</i>

04:53.918 --> 04:55.503
Imagine opening that box.

04:55.586 --> 04:59.424
Apparently, the finger reeked so badly,
a copywriter passed out.

04:59.507 --> 05:01.718
<i>This is what happens</i>
<i>when the owner of the newspaper</i>

05:01.801 --> 05:03.261
<i>has a blabbermouth brat for a son.</i>

05:03.344 --> 05:05.471
What else did your dad tell you?

05:05.555 --> 05:07.682
Everyone's worried
what else they'll find in their mail.

05:07.765 --> 05:10.059
The killer took Simon Soo's earring
and God knows what else.

05:10.143 --> 05:13.062
Next, they'll open a box with his cock
and the alleged Prince Albert.

05:14.314 --> 05:17.442
What is wrong with you?
He was murdered. That was our professor.

05:17.525 --> 05:19.319
<i>Who I suspect she was sleeping with.</i>

05:19.402 --> 05:20.737
Whoa. Relax. I was just--

05:20.820 --> 05:23.823
Just being crass about another human being
getting chopped to bits.

05:23.906 --> 05:26.326
No, it's pointless. You are disgusting.

05:28.411 --> 05:32.498
<i>She needs to talk to someone,</i>
<i>but I've got my hands full with you.</i>

05:37.003 --> 05:41.382
<i>Three hours since your last text.</i>
<i>Are you tired of playing with me already?</i>

05:42.258 --> 05:45.053
<i>Meanwhile,</i>
<i>I'm looking for clues wherever I can.</i>

05:47.096 --> 05:50.016
<i>It's the same news on a loop,</i>
<i>and until I've found you,</i>

05:50.099 --> 05:53.019
<i>I'm reminded</i>
<i>I'm not the only one looking for you.</i>

05:54.395 --> 05:57.523
<i>...which he frequented</i>
<i>along with many of his close friends.</i>

05:58.775 --> 06:03.279
<i>I assume the police are asking Kate</i>
<i>if Malcolm had enemies.</i> <i>Simon as well.</i>

06:03.362 --> 06:04.906
<i>And come to think of it,</i>

06:04.989 --> 06:08.910
<i>from the way she's acting, she'll be lucky</i>
<i>if they don't start suspecting her.</i>

06:08.993 --> 06:11.996
<i>Not a tear.</i>
<i>And she didn't even offer them tea.</i>

06:13.790 --> 06:14.791
<i>Ooh. Shit.</i>

06:24.634 --> 06:27.970
<i>What is that American expression?</i>
<i>Mind your own fucking business.</i>

06:28.054 --> 06:31.307
I'm sorry, the news about Malcolm...

06:31.390 --> 06:33.059
<i>Must be a terrible shock.</i>

06:35.520 --> 06:37.355
I wanted to offer condolences.

06:37.438 --> 06:40.358
<i>Save your breath. You'll need it</i>
<i>for when the police arrive.</i>

06:42.735 --> 06:44.695
-<i>She didn't.</i>

06:44.779 --> 06:46.155
<i>Oh, she did.</i>

06:50.743 --> 06:52.912
When was the last time
you saw Malcolm Harding?

06:55.915 --> 06:57.917
Ah, about a week ago.

06:58.000 --> 06:59.085
I think--

06:59.168 --> 07:03.422
He brought me home from a club.
His girlfriend might have mentioned that.

07:03.881 --> 07:08.302
Also at that club was Simon Soo.
Is that right?

07:09.679 --> 07:13.641
And you were at his show opening
the night he was killed.

07:13.724 --> 07:16.269
<i>What else did Kate tell them,</i>
<i>my favorite cereal?</i>

07:16.352 --> 07:17.186
That's right.

07:17.270 --> 07:20.231
You've become a fast fixture
in this social circle.

07:20.690 --> 07:23.818
Miss Galvin mentioned
you've been avoiding the police.

07:24.485 --> 07:25.611
<i>Of course she did.</i>

07:25.695 --> 07:30.658
That's-- Well, I thought
there might be a slight work-visa issue,

07:30.741 --> 07:34.620
-but the papers are in order now.
-It's not really our department.

07:36.164 --> 07:39.834
So when Professor Harding took you home,

07:39.917 --> 07:44.964
if I'm not mistaken, that makes you
the last person to see him alive.

07:45.047 --> 07:47.842
<i>Shit. Time to start dancing</i>
<i>as</i> <i>fast</i> <i>as</i> <i>I</i> <i>can.</i>

07:47.925 --> 07:49.760
Not sure that's true, actually.

07:51.512 --> 07:52.930
This is embarrassing.

07:53.014 --> 07:57.852
We both had too much to drink,
and Malcolm was telling me things

07:57.935 --> 08:00.229
that maybe he didn't mean to,

08:00.313 --> 08:02.440
like he found out Simon

08:02.523 --> 08:05.693
had been coercing artists
into making his paintings.

08:05.776 --> 08:10.781
I guess Malcolm gambled and was strapped,
so he was going to make Simon fix it.

08:10.865 --> 08:13.201
I took that to mean "blackmail."

08:14.994 --> 08:17.997
It feels wrong
to be speaking ill of the dead,

08:18.080 --> 08:22.376
but the news has been saying
this could be a serial killer, so...

08:24.879 --> 08:27.215
Maybe the real story is closer to home.

08:30.885 --> 08:33.513
-Anyone who can corroborate this?
-Blue Cahill, yeah.

08:33.596 --> 08:38.017
She's one of the artists
who Simon was taking advantage of.

08:39.310 --> 08:41.103
I heard she might be in rehab.

08:45.441 --> 08:48.152
Well, thanks again for the tea.

08:49.737 --> 08:52.865
If you think of anything else,
you'll let us know.

08:52.949 --> 08:56.410
Yeah, of course. Of course, yeah.
I'll show you out.

09:04.961 --> 09:06.879
<i>"That bitch sent the police</i>
<i>straight to you."</i>

09:06.963 --> 09:09.715
<i>What the fuck? Where the fuck are you?</i>

09:13.177 --> 09:15.680
<i>Show yourself, you coward.</i>

09:16.806 --> 09:18.641
<i>-"Kate's a threat.</i>

09:18.724 --> 09:20.851
<i>Life or death, one might say.</i>

09:22.103 --> 09:23.938
<i>You should take care of her."</i>

09:24.981 --> 09:27.733
<i>And here it is, your real game.</i>

09:29.694 --> 09:31.571
<i>You want me to kill Kate.</i>

09:35.116 --> 09:37.034
<i>No sign, no surveillance equipment.</i>

09:37.118 --> 09:40.246
<i>How many times am I gonna tear</i>
<i>my place apart for you?</i>

09:43.291 --> 09:45.751
<i>Obviously, I'm not going to kill Kate.</i>

09:45.835 --> 09:47.670
<i>But is she your next target?</i>

09:48.421 --> 09:51.090
<i>Last thing I need is playing bodyguard</i>
<i>to the ice witch who hates me.</i>

09:52.842 --> 09:54.844
<i>Keep it generic, noncommittal.</i>

09:57.346 --> 09:58.889
<i>"Kate won't be a problem."</i>

10:00.683 --> 10:02.977
<i>But if your eyes are on her,</i>

10:03.060 --> 10:04.645
<i>mine have to be too.</i>

10:06.689 --> 10:09.775
<i>I go where she goes.</i> <i>And I find you.</i>

10:24.165 --> 10:25.333
Nadia.

10:25.416 --> 10:27.126
Oh. Uh...

10:30.463 --> 10:31.297
Hi.

10:32.840 --> 10:35.176
-What are you doing here?
-I live around the corner.

10:35.259 --> 10:37.803
What are you doing sneaking around
the building of a murder victim?

10:40.640 --> 10:42.600
I'm looking for Malcolm's hide-a-key.

10:43.225 --> 10:46.896
-<i>She needs someone she can trust.</i>
-You left something in there?

10:47.438 --> 10:49.440
Fuck. Fuck.

10:51.484 --> 10:52.985
-Did he tell you?
-I guessed.

10:53.069 --> 10:54.820
I don't think it's common knowledge.

10:59.075 --> 11:01.035
I've written him something. Um...

11:02.787 --> 11:06.457
I've written him a letter
that I shouldn't have and it's in there.

11:06.540 --> 11:10.753
It's amongst all his things,
it's gonna be found and end up a headline.

11:10.836 --> 11:14.924
And then where does it leave me?
I'm completely publicly destroyed.

11:16.217 --> 11:19.178
-Smash my way in it is--
-No, don't. Don't do that.

11:19.261 --> 11:20.096
Um...

11:21.389 --> 11:24.183
-I'm friends with Kate.
<i>-Hardly, but I'll figure it out.</i>

11:25.434 --> 11:27.103
I'll get the letter for you.

11:31.941 --> 11:33.234
I won't break in.

11:35.027 --> 11:36.278
I won't break in yet.

11:42.868 --> 11:44.078
<i>Been there.</i>

11:47.623 --> 11:51.627
<i>Congratulations, the eat-the-rich killer</i>
<i>has managed to go viral.</i>

11:51.710 --> 11:54.672
<i>Unintended consequence</i>
<i>or did you mean to start a movement?</i>

11:54.755 --> 11:57.591
<i>More importantly,</i>
<i>how do I find you at Simon's funeral</i>

11:57.675 --> 12:00.469
<i>in a crowd adept at acting one way</i>
<i>when</i> <i>the</i> <i>cameras</i> <i>are</i> <i>on</i>

12:00.553 --> 12:02.346
<i>and another when they're in private?</i>

12:06.475 --> 12:11.772
<i>So the question becomes, "Whose grief</i>
<i>doesn't feel entirely genuine?"</i>

12:12.982 --> 12:16.610
<i>-Take Sophie Soo, for example...</i>
<i>-Please, in lieu of flowers,</i>

12:16.694 --> 12:20.698
<i>donate to hashtag "smiles for Simon Soo."</i>

12:20.781 --> 12:23.284
<i>...blatantly using grief</i>
<i>to gain followers and donations</i>

12:23.367 --> 12:25.744
<i>for an underprivileged</i>
<i>children's dental charity</i>

12:25.828 --> 12:28.914
<i>that doesn't seem to exist outside</i>
<i>of a hastily put-together website.</i>

12:30.541 --> 12:33.669
<i>Doesn't make her a killer,</i>
<i>but it does make me wonder.</i>

12:33.752 --> 12:39.008
<i>Of course, there's Kate. Must keep her</i>
<i>out of your crosshairs. From a distance.</i>

12:39.550 --> 12:43.179
<i>Then there's Phoebe whose years</i>
<i>of media experience</i> <i>have done little</i>

12:43.262 --> 12:47.099
<i>-to help her publicly process her grief.</i>
<i>-If you're watching this,</i>

12:47.600 --> 12:50.769
<i>help me find the remains</i>
<i>of my friend Malcolm.</i>

12:50.853 --> 12:54.231
<i>He liked corgis and soup.</i>

12:54.940 --> 12:59.195
<i>If you find any bits that belong to him,</i>

12:59.278 --> 13:00.946
<i>please call 999,</i>

13:01.655 --> 13:05.117
<i>and I promise you</i>
<i>you'll be heavily rewarded.</i>

13:05.201 --> 13:07.786
<i>She's a medicated mess</i>
<i>but not a murderer.</i>

13:08.412 --> 13:09.413
<i>What about Adam?</i>

13:09.497 --> 13:13.375
<i>Hard to get a read on him</i>
<i>and I know he's one to keep a secret.</i>

13:14.126 --> 13:16.504
<i>So which is he,</i>
<i>typical stunted American male</i>

13:16.587 --> 13:18.130
<i>or secret serial killer?</i>

13:18.881 --> 13:21.592
<i>Oh, and then there's Rhys Montrose.</i>

13:21.675 --> 13:25.137
<i>Allegedly days away</i>
<i>from declaring his candidacy</i> <i>for mayor.</i>

13:25.221 --> 13:26.680
<i>Savvy political move.</i>

13:26.764 --> 13:28.599
<i>Manipulating the public</i>
<i>by crying over a friend.</i>

13:28.682 --> 13:31.060
<i>Or is he here to manipulate me?</i>

13:50.704 --> 13:53.290
<i>I missed my funeral in Madre Linda,</i>
<i>but from what I read,</i>

13:53.374 --> 13:56.585
<i>it was a low-key affair,</i>
<i>so the exact opposite of this.</i>

14:00.839 --> 14:03.509
-You're here.
-<i>Now's my chance for a truce.</i>

14:03.592 --> 14:05.511
I have no desire
to hear what you have to say,

14:05.594 --> 14:06.929
and I don't know why you've come.

14:07.012 --> 14:08.389
Phoebe invited me.

14:10.266 --> 14:11.684
<i>So much for a ceasefire.</i>

14:14.311 --> 14:18.691
<i>Away from the paparazzi,</i>
<i>they seem more terror-stricken than sad.</i>

14:18.774 --> 14:21.485
If this is a murder-the-rich-
to-get-back-at-the-poor thing,

14:21.569 --> 14:24.113
I hope you know
I inherited nothing but the castle.

14:24.196 --> 14:25.948
<i>Gemma, never not horrible,</i>

14:26.031 --> 14:28.701
<i>but hard to imagine her rousing</i>
<i>the ambition to murder.</i>

14:28.784 --> 14:32.204
<i>Then again, if she's you,</i>
<i>it's all an award-winning act.</i>

14:32.288 --> 14:34.331
Start wearing bulletproof vests.

14:34.415 --> 14:37.001
And destroy this silhouette?
I'd rather be dead.

14:37.084 --> 14:39.503
This is nonsense.
No one's trying to kill us.

14:39.587 --> 14:43.007
<i>Roald, he's not afraid</i>
<i>because he's you</i>

14:43.090 --> 14:45.843
<i>or just too arrogant</i>
<i>to see himself as mortal.</i>

14:47.803 --> 14:50.598
-How are you faring?
-Fine.

14:50.681 --> 14:52.391
You get Malcolm squared away?

14:53.017 --> 14:55.769
We managed to find a spot
near his grandmother

14:55.853 --> 14:58.772
where we can inter the finger.

15:00.274 --> 15:03.944
-I'm so very sorry--
-No, Roald, can we not? Showtime.

15:08.866 --> 15:12.202
<i>Protective or is it you taunting me?</i>

15:14.663 --> 15:16.916
How could I be friends with Simon Soo?

15:19.126 --> 15:24.381
Sure, you may have seen an interview
where he said something wildly off-color.

15:25.758 --> 15:27.092
Doubtless while naked.

15:31.013 --> 15:33.682
But we all wear different masks,
depending.

15:34.600 --> 15:38.145
And of course, parts of us
we can't bear to show to anyone.

15:38.228 --> 15:40.064
<i>What's behind Rhys's mask?</i>

15:40.731 --> 15:43.192
<i>He told me it doesn't take long</i>
<i>to get here from Berlin</i>

15:43.275 --> 15:45.736
<i>-so I can't rule him out.</i>
-What would it have done

15:45.819 --> 15:49.657
to the reputation of an edgy,
purportedly egomaniacal genius

15:49.740 --> 15:53.619
if you also knew he gave a third
of his earnings to charity?

15:54.536 --> 15:56.372
Or do anything for his sister?

16:01.293 --> 16:04.338
-Joan Didion wrote of mourning...
-<i>And he's about to run for mayor.</i>

16:05.005 --> 16:06.090
<i>Call me crazy.</i>

16:06.173 --> 16:09.385
<i>Feels like that will complicate lurking</i>
<i>anonymously to kill people.</i>

16:09.468 --> 16:11.053
"When we mourn our losses,

16:12.638 --> 16:15.015
we also mourn for better or for worse...

16:17.685 --> 16:19.353
-ourselves."
-<i>Fuck.</i>

